  <original-body>When using ActionMailer, if you use the view templates (i.e. invitation.text.plain.erb) ActionMailer forces @content_type to multipart/alternative, even if you have specified multipart/mixed as the content type.  This becomes problematic when attempting to send multipart/mixed - text/plain and text/calendar types (which is what most email clients need to both show the message and trigger that it is a calendar invite).

The following patch just checks to see if the content type was already set to a multipart type, and if so does not change @content_type.</original-body>
